<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-0496 </DOCNO><TEXT>A simple introduction is given to nuclear magnetic resonance and its usein imaging for diagnostic purposes in medicine. After outlining the physicalprinciples and historical aspects of NMR imaging, examples are givenof both types of scanners and the images produced. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>